%N A395268 Decimal expansion of 1/3 + sqrt(3)/(2*Pi).
%C A395268 The probability that a chord determined by a point uniformly selected at random in a disk and a direction independently and uniformly selected at random is longer than a side of an equilateral triangle inscribed in the disk (Székely, 1986).
%C A395268 The probability that a chord determined by a point uniformly selected at random on the circumference of a circle, and a second point independently and uniformly selected at random in the interior of this circle is longer than a side of an inscribed equilateral triangle (Funkenbusch, 1962).
%C A395268 Bertrand (1889) gave three possible definitions for a random chord, for which the corresponding probabilities are 1/3, 1/2, or 1/4.
%D A395268 Gábor J. Székely, Paradoxes in Probability Theory and Mathematical Statistics, Reidel, 1986, p. 47.
%H A395268 Joseph Bertrand, <a href="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k99602b/f65.item">Calcul des probabilités</a>, Gauthier-Villars, Paris, 1889, pp. 5-6.
%H A395268 W. W. Funkenbusch, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2688933">A New Probability Model for Bertrand's Paradox</a>, Mathematics Magazine, Vol. 35, No. 3 (1962), p. 144.
%H A395268 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BertrandsProblem.html">Bertrand's Problem</a>.
%H A395268 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bertrand_paradox_(probability)">Bertrand paradox (probability)</a>.
%H A395268 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395268 Equals 1 - A258147.
%e A395268 0.608997781044229358088996582489818054032026573516653...
%t A395268 RealDigits[1/3 + Sqrt[3]/(2*Pi), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395268 (PARI) 1/3 + sqrt(3)/(2*Pi)
